## Personalized Prioritization for This 38F ($300/mo Budget)

### Immediate (Months 1–3)
**Investment: ~$50–80**
1. **Sleep optimization** ($30–50 one-time)
   - Sleep tracking device (Oura Ring, $300 upfront but 1-yr ROI) OR free phone app
   - Sleep hygiene education + evening routine (no screen after 9 PM, dark room, consistent bedtime)
   - Target: 7–8 hours/night (adds ~1 week/month of glymphatic clearance)

2. **APOE genotyping** ($100–150, one-time)
   - Determines if aggressive prevention warranted vs. standard approaches
   - 23andMe health report (~$30) or clinical genetic testing

3. **Physical activity baseline** ($0–50)
   - Sedentary desk job = #1 modifiable risk
   - Start: 30 min/day brisk walking (free) or YouTube strength training
   - Target: 150 min/week moderate activity per WHO guidelines

### Secondary (Months 2–6)
**Investment: ~$50–100/mo sustained**
1. **Omega-3 supplementation** ($20–30/mo)
   - High-quality fish oil or algae-based (algae better if vegetarian): 2000 mg EPA+DHA/day
   - 6-month trial minimum before efficacy assessment

2. **Diet optimization** ($0 net, possibly saves money)
   - Mediterranean-style: more vegetables, fish, olive oil
   - Reduce simple carbs (pre-diabetic risk + amyloid accumulation link)

3. **Cognitive training** ($20–30/mo optional)
   - Lumosity, Duolingo, or free options (puzzles, learning new skill)

### Tertiary (Months 3–12, if APOE ε4+)
1. **Lion's Mane trial** ($20–40/mo)
